# Documentation rules

## Authority

- [docs/SPEC.md](mdc:docs/SPEC.md) is the source of truth for behavior, AWS integration, and security.
- [docs/ROADMAP.md](mdc:docs/ROADMAP.md) defines what ships in each version; do not mark features done in ROADMAP until implemented.
- [README.md](mdc:README.md) is the user-facing summary; keep command tables aligned with `src/commands.ts` and SPEC §9.

## When to update

- CLI flags, commands, or default output → update README + SPEC (+ ROADMAP if version scope changes).
- New architectural decision after design review → add `docs/adr/NNNN-slug.md` (sequential numbering).

## Terminology (consistent across docs)

| Term | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| actual | Billing-backed cost (CUR, CE) |
| estimate | Monitoring / price-list based, not finalized billing |
| principal | IAM entity ARN in CUR `line_item_iam_principal` |
| source | CLI `--source` or report header data origin |

## Language

- README, SPEC, ROADMAP, ADRs: Japanese.
- AGENTS.md: English (agent instructions).
- Code identifiers and CLI flags: English.

## Avoid

- Documenting v0.2+ commands as shipped when only listed in ROADMAP.
- Promising security boundaries for `--principal self` beyond SPEC (UX filter in direct mode).
